Speaker 2: Okay, so you did place this order, and there already is a tracking number,

Speaker 2: Go ahead.

Speaker 1: Okay. So our computer system also keeps record.

Speaker 2: We actually have a tech guy where a big part of his job is he literally watches,

Speaker 1: like can see you through your phone going through and selecting the different options on the website

Speaker 2: when you place the order. Ordering with us is a really extensive process.

Speaker 1: So anytime banks reach out to us, we always have extensive evidence to show that you did,

Speaker 2: in fact, order what you ordered.

Speaker 1: Now, I do understand that the branded Viagra pills are very expensive.

Speaker 2: They are very expensive from Pfizer. They are very expensive from us who sell Pfizer.

Speaker 1: Yes, that is a fact, and there is nowhere you can go to get them cheaper.

Speaker 2: Now, the AGB is a much better deal, and it is a very good product.

Speaker 1: So I am sorry that I don't have any notes about you emailing us to change the order.

Speaker 2: I am sorry if that didn't get changed in time, which it sounds like was the issue.

Speaker 1: So I do really apologize about that.

Speaker 2: But yes, I mean you did place the order because there is a note that says,

Speaker 1: new consult started while changing order.

Speaker 2: I don't care. Okay, you finished speaking.

Speaker 1: Right.

Speaker 2: Yes, you finished speaking.

Speaker 1: You reached out to us to ask to change the order that you did place.

Speaker 2: No.

Speaker 1: You certainly do not have to go to the post office.

Speaker 2: You certainly do not have to do any big process.

Speaker 1: It's just the minute you receive it in a few days,

Speaker 2: you just have to write return to sender on the package.

Speaker 1: And as long as you don't open it, it will come right back to us

Speaker 2: and we can refund you immediately.

Speaker 1: But that is our protocol when somebody places an order and the order has been shipped

Speaker 2: is we are super happy to refund you any time.

Speaker 1: If you are not happy with the order, we just have to receive it back.

Speaker 2: I'll be happy to do that.

Speaker 1: But cancel my account.

Speaker 2: I want nothing to do with this company because what you've said is all crap.

Speaker 1: I didn't order anything.

Speaker 2: I simply asked a question.

Speaker 1: How can I change my previous prescription to the AGV?

Speaker 2: That's all I did.

Speaker 1: Anything else that was detected by this person is incorrect.

Speaker 2: I never got a price.

Speaker 1: I never got anything other than a text message that says your order has shipped.

Speaker 2: So please delete my account and I'll take care of this through social media

Speaker 1: and everything else and I'll return the package.

Speaker 2: And you'll never get paid because American Express will never pay this bill.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: It is my job to let you know that if you did file a dispute with us,

Speaker 1: you do get blacklisted from ever ordering with the company.

Speaker 2: It's their big boss's very special rule.

Speaker 1: That's terrific.

Speaker 2: That's the best thing you can do.

Speaker 1: That she's very strict about.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Excellent.

Speaker 2: So I've informed you and I will leave a note in your profile that you're aware.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Did you inactivate my account?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: I don't want anybody else dealing with this ever again.

Speaker 1: Absolutely.

Speaker 2: Of course.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Yes, John.

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: Have a great day.

Speaker 1: Bye.

Speaker 2: You too.

Speaker 1: Good luck.
